title: ‘Not the brain of Ireland’: Douglas Murray blasts ‘dimwit’ actress for Gaza comments
description: Author Douglas Murray blasts “dimwit” Irish actress and pro-Palestinian activist Denise Gough on her comments surrounding the Gaza peace plan.  “She strikes me as not being the brain of Britain or indeed of Ireland,” Mr Murray told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “You can see her sort of struggling for the next thought, it almost is written across her forehead as she does that.  “She probably can’t point to any of the places in question on a map.  “Perhaps it’s not a lack of Palestinian voices, it’s a lack of her being able to hear anything she doesn’t want to hear.”

title: Chris Bowen not interested in Tomago smelter energy cost blame game
description: Sky News host Sharri Markson assesses Energy Minister Chris Bowen’s blame game surrounding the Tomago aluminium smelter potential shutdown over rising energy costs.  “As you know the plant could close by 2028 because of rising electricity costs,” Ms Markson said.  “How much is the government … to blame for Tomago’s possible closure?”

title: Liberal Party in a ‘world of pain’ as support wanes
description: Sky News host Paul Murray says the Liberal Party is in a “world of pain” as support dips for the party while One Nation sees a surge.

title: ‘Higher than forecast’: Questions loom for RBA over inflation uptick
description: Sky News host Sharri Markson raises questions about the concerning inflation figures hitting Australia.  “An interest rate cut next week is looking unlikely after data today showed inflation is rising,” Ms Markson said.  “1.3 per cent in the September quarter, taking the annual rate up to 3.2 per cent.”

title: ‘Worst Victorian premier since the last one’: Jacinta Allan lashed over state issues
description: Sky News host James Macpherson highlights how Bill Shorten holds back some praise for Victorian Premier Jacinta Allan.  “Translation, if she weren’t in my party, I’d be saying what everyone else is,” Mr Macpherson said.  “She is the worst Victorian premier since, well, the last one.”

title: ‘Brilliant idea’: Keir Starmer wants migrants ‘out’ of hotels within 12 months
description: Sky News host James Macpherson delivers an update on the UK government asylum seeker hotel debacle.  “Starmer’s just come out with a brilliant idea,” Mr Macpherson said.  “Within 12 months they want all asylum seekers out of hotels and into military bases.”

title: ‘Punt up your money’: Meghan Markle cashes in on new candle
description: Sky News host Caleb Bond describes Meghan Markle’s newly released candle.  “She’s released a candle, I am sure you will be glad to hear it,” Mr Bond said.  “If you can bear to punt up your money for it.”

title: ‘No one's allowed to mine’: NSW opal mining town hit with native title claims
description: White Cliffs Miners’ Association President Troy Karkoe expresses frustration over government red tape resulting from native title claims.  The town faces dire challenges due to claims hindering mining activities and tourism.  “No one’s allowed to mine,” Mr Karkoe told Sky News host Andrew Bolt.  “It’s demoralised the town.  “We're losing.”

title: ‘The surge is on’: One Nation support doubles since federal election
description: On tonight’s episode of Paul Murray Live, Sky News host Paul Murray analyses One Nation support, cost of living, US politics and more.

title: Hamas needs to be ‘utterly and completely’ militarily defeated to maintain peace
description: Deputy Assistant to the US President Sebastian Gorka argues Hamas needs to be “utterly and completely” militarily defeated in order for the Middle East to maintain peace.  “Hamas is about Jihad, Hamas is about killing all those who do not ideologically agree with them or enslaving them,” Mr Gorka told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “Unless Hamas is completely excised from that community, unless there is a new political class … there is no hope for the people of either Gaza or the West Bank.”

title: Trump Deputy Assistant accuses Hamas of waging ‘psychological warfare’ against Israel
description: Deputy Assistant to the US President Sebastian Gorka accuses Hamas of implementing “psychological warfare” against the people of Israel.   “If you just look at the public reporting for the last 20 years … let’s be very clear, a form of psychological warfare has been implemented against the people of Israel,” Mr Gorka told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “The psychological exploitation will likely continue, but they’re messing with the wrong president and at the same time, they’re also messing with the wrong prime minister in the form of Benjamin Netanyahu.”

title: Megyn Kelly reacts to former Biden advisor Mike Donilon's ‘under oath’ court blunder
description: ‘The Megyn Kelly Show’ host Megyn Kelly highlights the “runaround” former senior Biden advisor Mike Donilon gave the court over his potential bonus if the former US president was re-elected.   “Sitting here under oath did not want to give it up,” Ms Kelly told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “But was forced to.”

title: ‘Half comatose nursing home patient’: Megyn Kelly mocks Biden’s failed re-election bid
description: ‘The Megyn Kelly Show’ host Megyn Kelly reacts to top Biden advisor Mike Donilon being forced to admit he would have received a $4 million bonus if the former US president was re-elected.   “They were trying to ferret out what the incentives were on his inner circle to keep this, you know, half comatose, elderly, nursing home patient upright and get him over the finish line in a presidential election,” Ms Kelly told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “He [Mike Donilon] was being paid $4 million to work on the campaign … and he had a $4 million bonus waiting for him if Joe Biden won.  “When you see the videotape of him hemming and hawing in an effort to avoid having to answer the question, it is so telling … he is like a deer in the headlights, trying to pretend he doesn’t understand.”

title: Deputy Assistant to Trump calls out Kevin Rudd’s anti-Trump tweets in first meeting
description: Deputy Assistant to the US President Sebastian Gorka reveals he confronted US Ambassador Kevin Rudd over his past anti-Trump tweets during their first meeting.  “In my first meeting with your Ambassador, I brought up his tweets against the President, just to make sure he understands who we are and that we have very long memories and the internet is forever,” Mr Gorka told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “I brought up his importune tweets and comments in our first meeting together … you make your bed, and you lie in it.”

title: ‘Laughable’: Megyn Kelly blasts Democrats for backtracking on Trump-Hitler comparisons
description: ‘The Megyn Kelly Show’ host Megyn Kelly responds to Democrats walking back comparisons between US President Donald Trump and Adolf Hitler.   “There are 10,000 sound bites of them saying, you know who else did what Trump is doing? Adolf Hitler,” Ms Kelly told Sky News host Paul Murray.   “Which, by the way, is a big deal, up until Trump that was a hard no in American conversation … because he was, of course, uniquely evil.  “The left has run rampant with it in the Trump era … so the fact that they want to whitewash it now and hope that we have forgotten is just kind of laughable.”
